Code Organization

Extracted signal generation into a reusable library (lib/ckp_gen): CkpGenerator.h/.cpp provide GapPosition, SignalConfig, IGenerator, and TimerCkpGenerator. // Encapsulates ISR-based slot generator into a clean API: begin(pin), apply(cfg), start(), stop(), plus safe getters (readCkpLevel, readGapWindow, getSlotPeriodUs). Keeps timing and GPIO toggling internal and synchronized via portMUX critical sections.
Updated src/main.cpp to include CkpGenerator.h and stop defining generator types/classes locally. // Avoids ODR/redefinition; we wrapped old in-file IGenerator/TimerCkpGenerator under #if 0 and switched to library symbols.
Serial CLI Enhancements

Added a friendly CLI with help, status, patterns, prompt, and aliases. // New helpers: printHelp, printPatterns, printStatus, printPrompt, and improved pollSerialForDemo. Supports help/?/h, status, patterns, bare-number RPM (e.g., 1500), and aliases (rpm=, set rpm, p, pat, etc.). After each command, prints confirmation + > prompt.
Kept logic of signal generation unchanged; only interaction scheme improved. // Manager still consumes CtrlMsg via FreeRTOS queue; CLI only produces messages.
LVGL UI Layer

Added a minimal LVGL UI library (lib/ui_lvgl): ui_lvgl.h/.cpp. // Public API: ui_init(on_pattern_cb, on_custom_cb) and ui_task_handler(). Creates two pages: main (preset dropdown + “Custom…” button) and custom (text boxes for rpm, teeth, pmiss, nmiss, pos, lvl with Apply/Back).
Preset selection dispatches on_pattern_cb(index); custom Apply parses user inputs, clamps ranges, builds SignalConfig, and dispatches on_custom_cb(&cfg). // Keeps UI as a producer of sanitized inputs; business logic remains in manager.
Main Wiring

Registered UI callbacks in setup() to send control messages: // on_ui_pattern: sends MSG_SET_PATTERN with payload.val = idx. on_ui_custom: sends MSG_SET_CUSTOM with payload.cfg = cfg. Integrates seamlessly with the existing queue/manager task.
Added ui_task_handler() in loop() to service LVGL. // LVGL requires periodic lv_tick_inc() and lv_timer_handler(); helper wraps both and is called once per loop iteration.
Display Driver Note

Implemented a stub LVGL display driver (no-op flush) to compile and run LVGL core without real panel. // In ui_lvgl.cpp we register a disp_flush_stub with a small draw buffer (320x10). Replace with your actual display/touch driver to render on hardware (e.g., ILI9341/ST7789/RGB panel). The UI structure remains the same; only driver glue changes.
PlatformIO Configuration

Added LVGL dependency to [env:esp32-s3-n4r8]. // platformio.ini now includes lib_deps = lvgl/lvgl@^8.3.11 under the S3 environment. Existing serial monitor settings retained; S3 env already runs at 921600 baud and uses PSRAM settings.
Concurrency and Safety

ISR/critical sections unchanged: generator toggles GPIO via REG_WRITE inside timer ISR, protected with portENTER_CRITICAL_ISR. // Ensures deterministic timing and no data races on shared state (_pinHigh, _gapWindow, etc.).
Control plane unchanged: producer(s) (CLI, UI) enqueue CtrlMsg to gCtrlQ; managerTask applies configuration on the generator. // Decouples UI/CLI from timing-critical generation; maintains safe handoff between tasks/ISRs.
